The paper discusses the evaluation of the inference capabilities of different components on mobile SoCs for Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) inference, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) domains. The paper also explores the performance limit of the mobile SoCs by synergistically engaging all the components concurrently, which involves system-level optimization and control, falling under the systems and control (cs.SY) domain. Finally, the paper discusses the power-performance behavior of the different components, which involves hardware design and optimization, falling under the architecture (cs.AR) domain.
